# identity/ssh/identities/none -- no-op SSH identity.
#
# Symlinked as ~/.ssh/identities/active when identity.ssh = "none".
# Included via the Include directive in identity/ssh/config -> ~/.ssh/config.
# Side effects: none. No host-specific configuration is applied.
#
# Purpose: ensures the Include ~/.ssh/identities/active line in the main config
# resolves to a real file. This avoids any "Include of missing file" ambiguity
# across SSH versions (RESEARCH Pitfall 5). The file is intentionally comment-only;
# no Host blocks or directives are set.
